rest_of_day_open: I can see the light at the end of the tunnel for the weekend which makes me very happy. Unfortunately I know there is going to be a lot of work and business the rest of this afternoon. Once I get over that hump it'll be all good! I hope my daughter is in a good mood though, she was a little cranky last night.
critical_positive: I think we found a connection as parents trying to juggle work and parenting at home during the pandemic. We discussed those issues and challenges almost entirely during the conversation. That was good to do though, because I haven't really had the opportunity to talk about those things with many other people. I liked that.
critical_negative: I think we both knew that we might not have as many other things in common besides that single topic of parenthood. She seemed a little older and also had two children of an older age than myself. She lived in Northern KY while I'm in a major urban area. I think we both decided to stick to what we knew was a commonality instead of expanding scope.

rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going quickly. I have several things to accomplish and that always helps the time go faster. The kids are home with me and we are preparing for back-to-school so that is also keeping us busy. I will admit, I'm looking forward to the weekend, though.
critical_positive: The person I just had a conversation with was very intelligent and able to carry on a competent exchange. We had several similarities in our lives and that helped give us things to talk about. He was interesting and I enjoyed asking him questions about his background and current life.
critical_negative: The person I just had a conversation with was often looking off the screen, to one side or another. It didn't effect our conversation verbally but it was a little distracting, at times. There were also a few instances where we kind of ran out of things to talk about but I quickly asked him another question and the conversation once again began to flow.
